law.text:
This subtitle does not apply to:
reinsurance;
a group annuity purchased under a retirement plan or deferred compensation plan established or maintained by an employer, including a partnership or sole proprietorship, or employee organization, or by both, other than a plan that provides individual retirement accounts or individual retirement annuities under § 408 of the Internal Revenue Code;
a premium deposit fund;
a variable annuity;
an investment annuity;
an immediate annuity;
a deferred annuity contract after annuity payments have begun;
a reversionary annuity; or
an annuity contract that is delivered outside the State through an insurance producer or other representative of the insurer issuing the contract.
